                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           SPORT BRIEFS
                                                        
	India rsquo;s tour on, says PCB  Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) Friday heaved a sigh of relief after the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) assured it that the Indian cricket team would tour Pakistan for the series early next year irrespective of the security situation in the country. 
  ldquo;The Indians have no issues about the tour and the itinerary is confirmed, rdquo; PCB director general Saleem Altaf said after discussing the matter with BCCI officials in New Delhi this week on the sidelines of a two-day meeting of the 2011 World Cup organising committee.    
	 Test venue  Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board on Friday said it might have to drop Rawalpindi as a venue for the Test series against India because of the slow pace of construction. Saleem Altaf, director-general of the board, said the Rawalpindi Test might be shifted to Faisalabad.    
